    "Evaluation on Medical Image Understanding Benchmarks Medical text pretraining enhances downstream medical image understandingWe demonstrate that continued pretraining on medical texts also provides a better foundation for subsequently adapting medical LLMs to the visual domain.",
    "Our evaluation tests MEDITRON-V on four different medical visual question-answering datasets: PMC-VQA [42], VQA-RAD [43], SLAKE [44], and PATH-VQA [45], which cover radiology and histology, and different imaging methods (e.g., CT scans, MRI, Tomography).",
    "We show an overview of MEDITRON-V's performance in Figure 3 On all four benchmarks, MEDITRON-V (7B) outperforms the Llama-2-V (7B) baseline, as well as Med-PaLM M (562B), a state-of-the-art commercial LMM that has significantly more parameters.",
    "Med-PaLM M scores are taken from its associated report [41].commercial Med-PaLM M (562B) model, MEDITRON-V achieves higher F1 scores across all benchmarks (3.3% on average), though this improvement varies for different metrics.",
    "In Supplementary Table 3, we provide a more comprehensive performance comparison between MEDITRON-V and other baseline medical LMMs [41,46]."
  ],
